<def f='linux-4.14.y/include/linux/pci.h' l='2276' ll='2288' type='bool pci_is_thunderbolt_attached(struct pci_dev * pdev)'/>
<doc f='linux-4.14.y/include/linux/pci.h' l='2268'>/**
 * pci_is_thunderbolt_attached - whether device is on a Thunderbolt daisy chain
 * @pdev: PCI device to check
 *
 * Walk upwards from @pdev and check for each encountered bridge if it&apos;s part
 * of a Thunderbolt controller.  Reaching the host bridge means @pdev is not
 * Thunderbolt-attached.  (But rather soldered to the mainboard usually.)
 */</doc>
